insert into items (id, cycle_id, assessment_id, qm_question_id, wording, major_element, sub_element, demand_level, max_score, status) values
  ('2dce36c0-cbe3-5a3e-b18a-c4bc14c9b569', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785246', 'Solar-powered irrigation projects The following stimulus has 3 questions. This is the 3rd. A study compares solar-powered irrigation projects in Kenya, India, and Morocco . It shows installation costs, annual water output, and annual energy savings to help governments decide which projects to invest in. Region Installation Cost (USD) Annual Water Output (m³) Annual Energy Savings (kWh) Kenya 14,250 9,500 3,150 India 15,600 10,400 3,600 Morocco 18,750 12,500 4,200 In Morocco : The annual energy savings are updated based on real life conditions: The first 3,000 kWh of savings are increased by 15% due to system improvement. For the remaining savings, only 80% is increased by 10% due to system improvement. After all earlier changes only 85% of the savings can be counted due to downtime. The system cannot save more than 4,000 kWh per year. What are the actual annual energy savings (kWh)? Round to the nearest whole number.', 'Numerical and quantitative reasoning', 'Applying mathematical operations', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('e9176780-ee64-5260-8b9c-a0190968d482', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785249', 'Welcome to the G12++ Applicable Maths section Here, you can show how confident you are in applying mathematics to solve problems. You have 90 minutes to answer exam questions. All questions are multiple-choice. At the end, there will be a short 5-minute survey. How can you do your best? Manage your time: <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559685&quot;:270,&quot;', NULL, NULL, 'D1', 0, 'active'),
  ('b15ca233-90a5-5e0a-b0d9-4d56d352c68f', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002784564', 'You have $50 to join a gym. At the beginning you pay a one-time registration fee of $5 . Then you pay $12 each month to use the gym. How many full months can you use the gym?', 'Functional algebra and logical thinking', 'Solving problems using algabraic thinking', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('db9d56ba-250d-5216-b0ba-6d74cf478561', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002784566', 'There is a rectangular room, with a size of 8 m × 6 m. You want to lay a carpet in the center that leaves a 1 m border on all sides. What is the area of the carpet?', 'Spatial and geometric reasoning', 'Interpreting shapes and measurements', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('e4557b93-793c-5e6e-a806-9d8308742a24', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785002', '4 friends go for a run. Each person runs at a constant speed. The graph shows the distance each person has run at a specific time. Who is the fastest runner?', 'Graphical literacy and visual data interpretation', 'Using visual data', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('6d6fa80d-d43c-51da-8fa1-4db56addf5c8', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785560', 'Welcome to the G12++ English as Second Language section You have 180 minutes to answer all exam questions. What to expect: There will be 3 sections: listening, reading and writing. There will be both multiple choice as well as open-ended questions. At the end, there will be a short 5-minute survey. <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559731&quot;:0,&quot;335559737&quot;', NULL, NULL, 'D1', 0, 'active'),
  ('21748c49-e4d9-56a7-bd76-df2f2d65c55c', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785004', 'You bought 12 dozen eggs for $0.20 each. You sell each egg for a 15% profit. Glossary: A dozen is a unit of quantity representing twelve (12) items. What is the total profit of all eggs?', 'Functional algebra and logical thinking', 'Recognizing and using patterns and relationships', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('279f6b72-be3b-5477-9b5c-35682b75d714', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002721869', 'This is a practice listening comprehension question. It will not count to your final mark. Listen to the audio below and follow the instructions you have just read. Remember, you can only press ''play'' on each audio copy once . The answer options will be on the question pages after this. 1 st audio copy: 2 nd audio copy – this is your final listening attempt: The questions for this audio are below: When should you leave the audio page? How can you pause the audio while listening to the file? When should you listen to the second copy of the audio? I have listened to the full audio.', NULL, NULL, 'D1', 0, 'active'),
  ('b3b33603-4927-5ff0-bb28-8bf1ed7f610a', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785006', 'You are making tomato pasta with cheese for 4 people. The recipe says each person needs: 80 g of pasta 60 g of tomato sauce 40 g of cheese Prices: Pasta: $2.60 per 200 g pack Tomato sauce: $2.40 per 300 g jar Cheese: $3.80 per 100 g pack The sizes of the packs and jar are the only options available. How much will you pay to buy the ingredients?', 'Numerical and quantitative reasoning', 'Applying mathematical operations', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('c0a1b54d-e8d4-557c-9812-239f5240cd94', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785306', 'Welcome to the G12++ Life Success Skills section Here, you can show how confident you are in applying essential (soft) skills to potential scenarios. This section is based on the skillsbuilder.org framework. You have 60 minutes to answer exam questions. All questions are multiple-choice questions, based on a short scenario. At the end, there will be a short 5-minute survey. How can you do your best? <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559731&quot;:0,&quot;335559737&quot;:0,&quot;335562764&quot;:2,&quot;335562765&quot;:1,&quot;33556276', NULL, NULL, 'D1', 0, 'active'),
  ('aab61af6-ef71-5139-9ec4-4019d130fc5d', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785009', 'You want to buy some notebooks. Each notebook costs $2.80 . For every 6 notebooks , there is a discount of 1/5 of the total cost. How much do you pay for 18 notebooks?', 'Functional algebra and logical thinking', 'Recognizing and using patterns and relationships', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('6ea892f4-bfda-59c2-90a4-b69642a4a121', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785014', 'For 40 days, you record when you arrive at work. On 2 days, you arrived late. On 6 days, you arrived on time. On the other days, you arrived early. What is the probability that you will arrive early ?', 'Data, probability and decision-making', 'Applying probability and statistical reasoning', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('adb66475-d13b-55f6-8578-8f11785faa03', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785011', 'You start a YouTube channel and track the total number of followers at the end of each month. At the end of each month, your total number of followers increases by the same amount. The monthly increase is half of the number of followers you had at the end of the first month. At the end of the 16th month, you had 7514 followers in total. What was the monthly increase?', 'Functional algebra and logical thinking', 'Recognizing and using patterns and relationships', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('dfb5ae43-4c24-55dd-a99d-dd3e46066b4d', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785012', 'You invest some money for one year. You invest $200 in Plan A which offers 5% interest per year. You invest the rest of your money in Plan B which offers 8% interest per year but carries a higher risk. From both plans, at the end of the year, you have a total of $36 of interest. How much money did you invest in Plan B ? Round to the nearest dollar.', 'Functional algebra and logical thinking', 'Recognizing and using patterns and relationships', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('e1a00a1d-db2c-5b86-8d8e-81ecc69c0b61', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785013', 'Your employer spends its $1,500 office budget as follows: Stationery: 0.3 of the total budget Software: 1/3 of the total budget Snacks: $175 Training: 1/4 of the total budget Which category receives the largest proportion of the total budget?', 'Numerical and quantitative reasoning', 'Understanding and using numbers', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('243807c4-a879-511e-8031-8848319b989a', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785018', 'A team of 3 employees handles 3 types of tasks daily: Task Time per Task Employees Required Tasks to Complete Reporting 2 hours 1 3 Client Calls 1.5 hours 2 4 Data Entry 1 hour 1 6 Each employee works 8 hours/day . This includes a 30 minutes lunch break. Can the team complete all tasks in one day?', 'Data, probability and decision-making', 'Understanding and interpreting data', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('83fd90d6-c525-5944-9e1c-0b85563e7793', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785019', 'A company tracks the weekly sales of 2 employees over 4 weeks: Which of the following statements is true?', 'Graphical literacy and visual data interpretation', 'Reading and interpreting graphical information', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('a6c87e6e-2d02-5eb5-8924-28fd7973ce3c', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785027', 'A company tracks the number of products sold by 1 employee over 4 weeks: Based on the chart, the largest percentage change in products sold took place during which of the following time periods?', 'Graphical literacy and visual data interpretation', 'Using visual data', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('fe8790dc-d3d8-5625-b034-02cd9b6d24a7', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '12b7a968-98eb-5a3f-8f6f-421fbaf0414e', '100002721415', 'الكتابة والتّعبير سيُطلب منك الإجابة على سؤالين كتابيين. لكلّ واحد، اكتب حوالي 250-200 كلمة. يجب أن: تجيب على السّؤال بشكل مباشر وواضح تنظّم أفكارك بطريقة مرتبة تستخدم مفردات وقواعد صحيحة، مع مراعاة الإملاء وعلامات التّرقيم حاول أيضًا أن: تشرح أفكارك باستخدام أمثلة أو أسباب <p data-ccp', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'active'),
  ('3a3e72da-e988-58db-9c6a-c85e2161f52e', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785036', 'The museum charges a fee of $10 for 1 visitor. But for groups, each additional visitor receives a $2 discount on the entrance fee. Which of the following expressions represents the total entrance fee for a group of n people?', 'Functional algebra and logical thinking', 'Recognizing and using patterns and relationships', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('351f5719-4474-500d-87e2-b44ac89a6858', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785053', 'An education NGO has 100 staff members working in 3 departments . Each department has a different number of staff. All staff members must complete AI training . The length of the course is different for each department. Which of the following statements is not true? The total training hours required for...', 'Graphical literacy and visual data interpretation', 'Reading and interpreting graphical information', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('717ece5b-0017-50bb-b119-06ac0a8df32d', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785074', 'You design a scale model of a real water storage tank. The scale model tank is made of two rectangular boxes: Lower box: 30 cm long × 15 cm wide × 10 cm high Upper box: 15 cm long × 15 cm wide × 10 cm high You use a scale of 1 : 5 . What is the volume of the real water storage tank in m 3 ?', 'Spatial and geometric reasoning', 'Interpreting shapes and measurements', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('dc66f00e-923e-50c1-a542-4f2d1e771ee7', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785081', 'A year group has 3 mathematics classes. They all take the same test. Class Number of candidates Mean of marks on test 1 35 89 2 40 75 3 25 60 Glossary: candidates = test-takers What was the mean mark for the whole year group? Round your answer to 1 decimal point.', 'Data, probability and decision-making', 'Understanding and interpreting data', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('d581b9d5-0d76-5c95-8078-2efa518669b0', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785086', 'The line graph shows the inflation rate (%) and unemployment rate (%) in a country from 2015 to 2022. What was the percentage increase or decrease for both inflation and unemployment from 2015 to 2022?', 'Graphical literacy and visual data interpretation', 'Reading and interpreting graphical information', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('48271f0c-6b67-5b02-adaa-466594598c1a', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785089', 'Your company needs to pay 1,200 USD for supplies, but the funds are in Lebanese Pounds (LBP). The bank allows you to exchange up to 500 USD worth of LBP per transaction. Exchange rate: 1 USD = 90,000 LBP (rounded) Commission: 1.5% of the USD amount exchanged Service fee: 10 USD per transaction How much LBP do you need to exchange to receive $1,200 USD while accounting for commissions and fees?', 'Numerical and quantitative reasoning', 'Understanding and using numbers', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('3622b472-d02c-57e8-ba32-79d24ab0891e', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785092', 'The store wants to increase stock for the product that has the fastest relative growth compared against the January starting point. Which product should it choose?', 'Graphical literacy and visual data interpretation', 'Using visual data', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('5376e305-6ab9-5db0-81b1-fcafa14906de', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785093', 'You work in a factory as a quality control manager, and you need to inspect electronic devices. The rate of devices that have problems is 2% . On a given day, you select 10 devices out of 100 produced for inspection. What is the approximate probability that at least 1 device has a major defect? Round to the nearest whole number.', 'Data, probability and decision-making', 'Understanding and interpreting data', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('55ee64ad-e20d-5aeb-8356-b7e76aae6415', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785097', 'You work in a small office that has 6 ordinary light bulbs , each consuming 60 watts every hour . 4 bulbs are used for 8 hours every day 2 bulbs are used for 6 hours every day Electricity costs $0.032 per kilowatt-hour (kWh). You replace all the bulbs with LED bulbs that consume 9 watts each . What is the total saving in electricity costs in a year (52 weeks)? Round to 2 decimal points.', 'Numerical and quantitative reasoning', 'Applying mathematical operations', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('d7bc0e43-2db3-5b1a-9221-86eaac7807bf', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785100', 'You arrange 9 identical rectangular tiles to make a 1 large rectangular tile. The length of the longer side of each small tile is 10 cm . What is the perimeter of the large tile?', 'Spatial and geometric reasoning', 'Interpreting shapes and measurements', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('1009352c-7629-5bf7-95e0-40832dedb49c', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785237', 'Solar-powered irrigation projects The following stimulus has 3 questions. This is the 1st. A study compares solar-powered irrigation projects in Kenya, India, and Morocco . It shows installation costs, annual water output, and annual energy savings to help governments decide which projects to invest in. Region Installation Cost (USD) Annual Water Output (m³) Annual Energy Savings (kWh) Kenya 14,250 9,500 3,150 India 15,600 10,400 3,600 Morocco 18,750 12,500 4,200 In Kenya: The annual energy savings (kWh) rise by 5% in the 2nd year of recording. Energy costs in the 2nd year are assumed to be 20 cents (USD) per kWh . What are the annual energy savings (in USD) in the 2nd year ? Round to the nearest whole number.', 'Numerical and quantitative reasoning', 'Applying mathematical operations', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('33b0e8fe-3d60-57d6-a0b8-1006454a9114', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785102', 'You work in a school and need to buy equipment for two activity groups. The cricket team needs x cricket bats , costing $25 each . The yoga group needs y yoga mats , costing $15 each . The total budget is $600 , and the school wants to buy three more cricket bats than yoga mats . How many cricket bats and yoga mats can you buy?', 'Functional algebra and logical thinking', 'Solving problems using algabraic thinking', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('70d60899-baac-5dba-99ed-0dda03a46ae5', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785098', 'Investigating fish population size The following stimulus has 2 questions. This is the 2 nd . You work in a pet shop. You notice some new tropical fish are dying in their water tank. Your boss suggests that it might be because of changes in the water''s concentration of dissolved oxygen (mg/L). She asks you to check. You do some research and find a graph showing the relationship between dissolved oxygen concentration in different fish tanks, and the number of live tropical fish surviving in each tank. The food supply and temperature of each tank is kept the same. You read that normally, tropical environments have 7-9 mg/L oxygen, so 8mg/L is used as a', 'Evaluate and design scientific inquiry', 'Using scientific processes and investigation', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('ee0e21dd-cb20-5d29-bf66-8af42154455a', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785105', 'A university tracked weekly study hours and average exam scores (%) for 3 programmes over 4 weeks. The graphs below summarise the data: Which statement best describes the relationship between study hours and exam scores?', 'Graphical literacy and visual data interpretation', 'Reading and interpreting graphical information', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('c7ba7100-d4ac-59cb-809d-4990f39af055', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785119', 'A school tracks student enrolment in 2025: Faculty Students Classroom size Science 480 1 classroom per 25 students Arts 420 1 classroom per 20 students Engineering 360 1 classroom per 30 students For 2026, the school expects a 10% growth in all faculties . Each faculty must have at least one extra classroom for labs or workshops. How many classrooms are needed for 2026 in total?', 'Data, probability and decision-making', 'Understanding and interpreting data', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('b9e663c2-7ef0-5d2b-9d29-d5b5ccd7ffc2', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785120', 'A business school in a university has 3 courses: Finance Marketing Management The department must allocate hours for each subject under these 3 independent rules: Finance is 5 hours more than twice Marketing. Management is 10 hours less than Finance. The sum of Finance and Marketing is twice the Management hours. What are the hours allocated to each course?', 'Functional algebra and logical thinking', 'Solving problems using algabraic thinking', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('01031726-a8ec-595f-be0c-1dc7a3e524b9', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785121', 'You are researching drought (long periods of very little rain) in Ethiopia. For each period, there are years with severe drought , moderate drought , or no drought . Time Period Severe Drought Moderate Drought No Drough t 1980-1989 20% 30% 50% 1990-1999 25% 35% 40% 2000-2009 30% 40% 30% 2010-2019 35% 45% 20% Researchers define “high agricultural risk” as a year with any level of drought (moderate or severe). You want to estimate the probability that a randomly selected year in the future will have high agricultural risk. Which conclusion is best supported by the data? The probability...', 'Data, probability and decision-making', 'Understanding and interpreting data', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('1786a8c7-7415-5fc2-bb15-b03f6e63558e', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785123', 'Your friend travels to Saudi Arabia and needs help choosing a mobile data plan. Prices are given in Saudi Riyals (SAR). Two plans are offered: Plan A offers a fixed monthly cost of 120 SAR plus 15 SAR per gigabyte (GB) of data used per month. Plan B offers a fixed monthly cost of 240 SAR plus 9 SAR per gigabyte (GB) of data used per month. For what minimum monthly data usage does Plan B become cheaper than Plan A?', 'Functional algebra and logical thinking', 'Solving problems using algabraic thinking', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('6a419a9e-0a45-5945-b6ed-c5142d6f593a', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785122', 'Your company runs marketing campaigns for 2 products, instant noodles and juice drink , over 4 months. The marketing spend and units sold are as follows: Glossary: Sales return per dollar = total units sold relative to total marketing spend. Over the 4 months, which product had the highest total sales return per total dollar spent, and what was that value? Round to 2 decimal points.', 'Graphical literacy and visual data interpretation', 'Using visual data', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('eba60c29-ce74-5255-9368-a59fe7067c78', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785124', 'You are renovating a bathroom. You need to tile the floor and walls. Floor dimensions: 3.6 m × 4.8 m Each floor tile covers 0.12 m² Wall tiles needed: 476 Tile cost: $0.24 each You decide to buy 10% more tiles (in case some tiles break). If you buy them today, the supplier will give you a 15% discount on the total purchase. If you wait until next week, you will not get a discount. You have $103 now. Your other clients will pay you as follows: $23 today $11 today $50 next week When can you afford to buy the tiles, and why? Round to the nearest dollar.', 'Numerical and quantitative reasoning', 'Applying mathematical operations', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('f7017648-d9d4-58f5-b186-b8834fdbd320', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002721870', 'This is a practice listening comprehension question. Choose your answer based on the audio you heard at the beginning of this section. When should you leave the audio page?', NULL, NULL, 'D1', 0, 'active'),
  ('44e393b0-10bc-5332-831b-7f0bf6189d1a', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002721873', 'This is a practice listening comprehension question. Choose your answer based on the audio you heard at the beginning of this section. How can you pause the audio while listening to the file?', NULL, NULL, 'D1', 0, 'active'),
  ('50404a65-3199-5951-be9d-8ceb2acdf5fd', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785125', 'Leen and Muamina are climbing a mountain. Leen is at an elevation of 1,480 m. Muamina is at an elevation of 1,620 m. The angle from Leen to Muamina is 22 degrees. Note: Consider the relationship between the angle of elevation (sin (θ), cos (θ) or tan (θ)), the vertical height, and the slope distance. What is the shortest distance on the trail for Leen to walk to catch up with Muamina?', 'Spatial and geometric reasoning', 'Interpreting shapes and measurements', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('c417d14e-c876-56d8-b604-191e6c8c650b', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785218', 'Large storeroom The following stimulus has 2 questions. This is the 1st. There is a large meeting room where you work with the following measurements: length is 4 m width is 3.5 m height is 2.5 m The door to the meeting room has a height of 2 m and a width of 1 m. There are two square windows in the meeting room, each with dimensions of 2 m. The meeting room walls are being painted. Paint is sold in cans, and each can covers 10 m² . What is the minimum number of paint cans needed to cover all the walls of the room?', 'Spatial and geometric reasoning', 'Interpreting shapes and measurements', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('0df4baac-a65d-525e-b193-affbbad26f89', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785109', 'Understanding pH indicators to help tomato plants thrive The following stimulus has 3 questions. This is the 3 rd . You want to know if the soil in your pot is good for planting tomatoes. You buy 4 indicators and add them to cups containing soil and water mixed together. Indicators are liquids that change colour. Depending on the colour change, they tell you how acidic (low pH, like lemon juice) or alkaline (high pH, like soap) the soil is. Details of your indicators are shown below: Indicator &nbs', 'Interpret evidence and data scientifically', 'Interpreting and inferring scientific data', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('0fd211c1-8b66-5dcf-8065-d9f3fea417bc', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785110', 'Investigating water bottle smells The following stimulus has 2 questions. This is the 1 st . Your classmate wants to test whether reusable plastic water bottles develop smells faster than disposable plastic bottles. She fills 1 reusable bottle and 1 disposable bottle with tap water She leaves the bottles in her backpack for 2 weeks Every 2 days, she smells each bottle and rates the smell from 0 (none) to 5 (strong). <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559731&quot;:0,&quot;335559737&quot;:0,&quot;335562764&quot;:2,&quot;335562765&quot;:1,&quot;335562766&quot;:4,&quot;335562767&quot;:0,&quot;335562768&quot;:4,&quot;335562769&quot;:0', 'Evaluate and design scientific inquiry', 'Understanding variables and validity', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('be5a495e-4264-51b1-8b89-fe7ed7266c52', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785220', 'Large storeroom The following stimulus has 2 questions. This is the 2nd. There is a large meeting room where you work with the following measurements: length is 4 m width is 3.5 m height is 2.5 m A heater is used to warm the meeting room. The heater can heat 10 m³ of air every 5 minutes . However, due to heat loss through walls and windows, 15% of the heat is lost every 10 minutes . How much air (in m³) is effectively heated after 20 minutes ? Round your answer to the nearest whole number.', 'Spatial and geometric reasoning', 'Interpreting shapes and measurements', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('3f3e9cde-e29c-58a7-8fe0-cd240ac77bd7', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785221', 'Pollution in the air The following stimulus has 3 questions. This is the 1st. The Air Quality Index (AQI) is a measure of pollution in the air. A study shows the percentage of people living in different AQI areas in a certain city. Air Quality Index (AQI) Percentage of population Low 10 Moderate 30 High 40 Very High 20 Another study shows the percentage of people with breathing problems in each AQI area in the same city. Air Quality Index (AQI) Percentage of people with breathing problems Low 5 Moderate', 'Data, probability and decision-making', 'Understanding and interpreting data', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('e223c84f-96f4-5d1c-9dfd-b43f7585b5d3', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785226', 'Pollution in the air The following stimulus has 3 questions. This is the 2nd. The Air Quality Index (AQI) is a measure of pollution in the air. A study shows the percentage of people living in different AQI areas in a certain city. Air Quality Index (AQI) Percentage of population Low 10 Moderate 30 High 40 Very High 20 Another study shows the percentage of people with breathing problems in each AQI area in the same city. Air Quality Index (AQI) Percentage of people with breathing problems Low 5 Moderate 9 High 15 Very High 25 </div', 'Data, probability and decision-making', 'Understanding and interpreting data', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('33fdd48e-75fd-59b1-b12a-ccee7a7c9721', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785231', 'Pollution in the air The following stimulus has 3 questions. This is the 3rd. The Air Quality Index (AQI) is a measure of pollution in the air. A study shows the percentage of people living in different AQI areas in a certain city. Air Quality Index (AQI) Percentage of population Low 10 Moderate 30 High 40 Very High 20 Another study shows the percentage of people with breathing problems in each AQI area in the same city. Air Quality Index (AQI) Percentage of people with breathing problems Low 5 Moderate 9 High 15 Very High 25 What percentage of the city’s people have breathing problems?', 'Data, probability and decision-making', 'Understanding and interpreting data', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('4d6add0c-d0fc-5a6a-bc13-85ad11570465', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'a23a1630-f7b6-51e7-ad74-cadc85838566', '100002785240', 'Solar-powered irrigation projects The following stimulus has 3 questions. This is the 2nd. A study compares solar-powered irrigation projects in Kenya, India, and Morocco . It shows installation costs, annual water output, and annual energy savings to help governments decide which projects to invest in. Region Installation Cost (USD) Annual Water Output (m³) Annual Energy Savings (kWh) Kenya 14,250 9,500 3,150 India 15,600 10,400 3,600 Morocco 18,750 12,500 4,200 In India : Only 80% of the annual water output reaches the crops. Water is evenly distributed across a square plot of a land at 1.25 m³ per m² per year. What is the approximate length of one side of the square plot? Round to the nearest whole number.', 'Numerical and quantitative reasoning', 'Applying mathematical operations', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('16a8a395-7305-53a9-a266-cc9bbe530bdf', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002721872', 'This is a practice listening comprehension question. Choose your answer based on the audio you heard at the beginning of this section. You should listen to the second copy of the audio…', NULL, NULL, 'D1', 0, 'active'),
  ('7d3ca984-48ef-5739-90cf-0e21f83e9f45', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785489', 'Audio page: 1 st audio copy: 2 nd audio copy – this is your final listening attempt: The questions for this audio are below: What is the key thing workers should do before moving something, according to the speaker? When objects are heavy or difficult to move, the speaker says it is important to ask for help. Why? What is most important for keeping the workplace safe, according to the speaker? I have listened to the full audio.', 'Listening comprehension', 'Item set home pages (audios)', 'D1', 0, 'active'),
  ('281bfec3-8e9e-5172-879a-0ca1b4e8afb4', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785541', 'Choose your answer based on the audio you heard at the beginning of this section. What is the key thing workers should do before moving something, according to the speaker?', 'Listening comprehension', 'Understanding meaning', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('544ae40d-5812-5fce-a876-3c7534457f8f', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785542', 'Choose your answer based on the audio you heard at the beginning of this section. When objects are heavy or difficult to move, the speaker says it is important to ask for help. Why?', 'Listening comprehension', 'Evaluating meaning', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('10bd5b64-9df0-508c-9eac-9b940e2ef448', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785543', 'Choose your answer based on the audio you heard at the beginning of this section. What is most important for keeping the work place safe, according to the speaker?', 'Listening comprehension', 'Interpreting speaking tone', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('46990fe1-4190-57d6-b005-52769f24abd1', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785549', 'Section 1 Short story: Migration Through a Young Man’s Eyes Kareem learned early to notice backgrounds rather than destinations. The colour of walls, the sound of streets at night, the way light shone through unfamiliar windows. These were what changed each season his family moved for work. Adults would always call the moves temporary, but Kareem stopped believing that word. He became used to packing quickly and carefully, keeping formal documents flat and other small objects safe, knowing they could impact important life outcomes. When he was able to attend government schools in the villages they passed through, he watched friendships become solid around him while his own remained unformed. Teachers spoke confidently about students setting goals for future years, yet Kareem measured time in days. 2 Responsibility had entered Kareem’s life quietly, without permission, even when he was a young boy. He translated instructions for his parents, calculated wages that never matched the costs of feeding a family and learned to read the silence of supervisors in the fields where he and his parents worked. Throughout his teenage years, his days followed a strict rhythm – working before sunrise, studying during the day, chores until late at night – leaving little space for rest or dreaming. Yet a quiet doubt followed him. He realised that he was enduring without choosing, moving forward because stopping felt dangerous rather than because the path felt right. He became unsettled: was perseverance, or pushing through despite challenges, still admirable if it had become automatic, leaving no space for change? This is what got him and his family through the most difficult moments, after all. <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:2,&quot;335551620&quot;:2,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335562764&quot;:4,&quot;33556276', 'Reading comprehension', 'Evaluating meaning', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('987fb585-682d-5ef6-ba2e-17392bf62b34', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785492', 'Audio page: 1 st audio copy: 2 nd audio copy – this is your final listening attempt: The questions for this audio are below: What does Ayah feel is the main benefit of living with a host family? Why does Ayah feel uneasy about meeting her host family? Why did Ayah decide to bring gifts for her host family? Why does Ayah repeat that she has been preparing for this moment “for so long”? I have listened to the full audio.', 'Listening comprehension', 'Item set home pages (audios)', 'D1', 0, 'active'),
  ('7e30e5b0-a4f7-5df8-a969-98b2fceede53', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785544', 'Choose your answer based on the audio you heard at the beginning of this section. What does Ayah feel is the main benefit of living with a host family?', 'Listening comprehension', 'Understanding meaning', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
