  ('bf53a67e-aeda-53c4-847c-9ce46dedc772', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785556', 'English as 2nd language – Reading Comprehension: In this section, you will find 5 texts to read, each followed by multiple-choice questions. How can you do your best? Manage your time: Keep an eye on the timer. Do not spend too long on one question. <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559685&quot;:270,&quot;335559731&quot;:-270,&quot;335559737&quot;:0,&quot;335562764&quot;:4,&quot;335562765&qu', NULL, NULL, 'D1', 0, 'active'),
  ('9ce36394-2b98-5f10-b8d3-e10453314c6d', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785333', 'Section 1 UNFPA Article: Supporting Older People Through Connection Maria Roșca, a 73-year-old widow in the Eastern European country of Moldova, lives on her own. Her children are working abroad. “I keep the TV and radio on, so I don’t feel completely alone,” she said. 2 Like many older people in Moldova, Ms Roșca faces life without close family nearby. Moldova has one of the highest emigration rates in Europe, with large numbers of young people moving to other countries. Therefore, many elderly people live in isolation. Nearly 20% of the country’s population is over the age of 60, and many are in poverty. 3 Dr Natalia Kanem, who works in international health, says ageing populations reveal deeper challenges in society such as age discrimination and unequal access to care. But older people should not be seen only as vulnerable. They also have valuable roles to play. “Older persons are the world’s fastest growing and least used asset,” said Dr Arun Maira. Many continue to contribute through paid work, volunteering, and sharing their knowledge. <td tabindex="0" data-celllook=', 'Reading comprehension', 'Understanding meaning', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
