  ('3984eaef-bc69-5690-918f-e843d7026da2', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785352', 'What is the author’s reason for including Slide 1: Introduction?', 'Reading comprehension', 'Understanding meaning', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('22ff6dc9-89e9-5e94-93eb-33cffb23c9d6', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785355', 'According to Slide 2: Market Overview, why is there a market need for this tutoring service?', 'Reading comprehension', 'Understanding meaning', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('32fcb2a4-6bdd-536d-b985-2ddb4a7847a2', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785356', 'How does Slide 3: Technology Used in the Program Structure convince readers about the benefits of technology in the program?', 'Reading comprehension', 'Evaluating meaning', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('d68a8b82-cf0a-54b7-a000-773f4ee78b41', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785357', 'According to Slide 4: Instructor Expertise, which of the following is not one of the benefits to students of having Arab tutors?', 'Reading comprehension', 'Understanding meaning', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('c7b50a4a-a09f-5617-b73e-05bf2f5a5f49', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785393', 'Section 1 Health journal: Why Steady-State Cardio and Cross-Training for Your Health and Wellbeing Many people struggle to make time for exercise. Today’s fast pace, busy schedules, and long to-do lists often push physical activity to the bottom of our priorities. In my view, the belief that exercise requires hours at the gym discourages many people from starting, as does the idea that a personal trainer is essential. In reality, staying active does not need to take over our days to be effective. Some people prefer steady-state cardio, such as jogging, cycling, or using an exercise bike at a comfortable, continuous pace. Others enjoy cross-training, which combines short, structured workouts that can be completed in under an hour. Both approaches show that exercise can fit into everyday life without being overwhelming. 2 Regular exercise plays a key role in keeping us strong and resilient. Steady-state cardio supports heart and lung health by keeping the heart rate elevated for longer periods, improving circulation and endurance. Cross-training, on the other hand, combines cardio with strength and functional movements, helping to build muscle while also improving stamina and balance. These forms of exercise help manage weight, support posture, and increase overall physical confidence. Over time, they reduce the risk of long-term conditions such as high blood pressure or type 2 diabetes, a link supported by many long-term health studies. Health experts often suggest around 30 minutes of moderate exercise on most days, which shows that consistency is often more important than extreme intensity. 3 <td', 'Reading comprehension', 'Understanding meaning', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
