  ('6bbf5f5c-4e89-5897-8c4d-3e4e12bbe5c2', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785405', 'Section 1 Posting - Volunteer Opportunity: After School Community Learning Programme Are you interested in supporting young learners while gaining useful experience? Volunteers are invited to join the After School Community Learning Programme, which supports students aged 8–12 as they explore specialised subjects in a safe and welcoming environment. Before beginning, volunteers attend an introductory session where they learn about programme routines, available materials, safety procedures, and expectations from experienced staff. This session helps volunteers understand how lessons are organised and what support is provided so they feel prepared. After the session, volunteers select their preferred subject and arrange their schedule through a form. All necessary supplies are provided. 2 The After School Community Learning Programme is ideal for volunteers who want to develop leadership and communication skills while working directly with children. Another initiative, the School Peer Observation Programme, takes a different approach. In that programme, participants attend lessons, complete observation checklists, and discuss teaching strategies during meetings to reflect on their experience, but they do not usually interact with students. In contrast, the After School Community Learning Programme offers an active teaching environment. Volunteers support small groups, guide students through learning tasks, and help them practise study routines during scheduled sessions. They also encourage focus and positive behaviour, contributing to an organised and supportive space. These regular interactions build students’ confidence and allow volunteers to contribute meaningfully to their community, which many previous volunteers have found rewarding. <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0