on', 'Evaluating meaning', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('aa0d5266-b4fa-56e8-adeb-83f7f64897cc', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785550', 'Section 1 Short story: Migration Through a Young Man’s Eyes Kareem learned early to notice backgrounds rather than destinations. The colour of walls, the sound of streets at night, the way light shone through unfamiliar windows. These were what changed each season his family moved for work. Adults would always call the moves temporary, but Kareem stopped believing that word. He became used to packing quickly and carefully, keeping formal documents flat and other small objects safe, knowing they could impact important life outcomes. When he was able to attend government schools in the villages they passed through, he watched friendships become solid around him while his own remained unformed. Teachers spoke confidently about students setting goals for future years, yet Kareem measured time in days. 2 Responsibility had entered Kareem’s life quietly, without permission, even when he was a young boy. He translated instructions for his parents, calculated wages that never matched the costs of feeding a family and learned to read the silence of supervisors in the fields where he and his parents worked. Throughout his teenage years, his days followed a strict rhythm – working before sunrise, studying during the day, chores until late at night – leaving little space for rest or dreaming. Yet a quiet doubt followed him. He realised that he was enduring without choosing, moving forward because stopping felt dangerous rather than because the path felt right. He became unsettled: was perseverance, or pushing through despite challenges, still admirable if it had become automatic, leaving no space for change? This is what got him and his family through the most difficult moments, after all. <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:2,&quot;335551620&quot;:2,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335562764&quot;:4,&quot;33556276', 'Reading comprehension', 'Synthesising and critically engaging with text', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('56aafa9c-a815-58c8-b0a5-82fc5de511aa', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785555', 'English as 2nd language – Writing and Expression: In this section, you will be asked to respond to 2 prompts. For each one, write a response of around 250 words. You must: answer prompts directly and clearly organise your response effectively use vocabulary, spelling, punctuation and grammar accurately and effectively. Try your best to also: <li data-charcodes="8226" data-font=', NULL, NULL, 'D1', 0, 'active'),
  ('a699597b-a659-522f-badf-27b0b72e8aaa', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '2ee55359-b5ce-5fa2-8710-cb048521502a', '100002785962', 'Have you answered all questions in this exam?', NULL, NULL, 'D1', 0, 'active'),
  ('608c2c5f-7663-5920-9c7b-f53c6e9cc814', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785312', 'During a group discussion, you notice a classmate who hasn’t shared any ideas yet. He looks like he wants to say something but is not sure when to join in. What is the best way to help him feel more able to join in?', 'Collaboration', 'Teamwork', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('657ea111-77d7-5331-a8ab-3782369360eb', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785329', 'You are explaining a group project to classmates who missed the lesson. Some students are familiar with the topic, but others are not. Which approach would be most appropriate?', 'Communication', 'Speaking', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('5d48b4a0-8813-5f18-9388-4362585c4c5a', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785337', 'During a group maths assignment, each member is responsible for completing one section by the deadline. A classmate asks if you’ve finished yours so she can combine all the parts, but you’re only halfway done. What is the most responsible action to take?', 'Collaboration', 'Teamwork', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('cbcc4c4f-9a78-57a6-96c4-04c2fe7158dc', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785347', 'Your study group at school is struggling because members have different schedules and rarely meet at the same time. The group wants to improve participation. What would be the best first step?', 'Creative Problem Solving', 'Problem Solving', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('5a889388-2f3e-5e79-a41b-66ba3df569e1', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785350', 'During a local cricket club meeting, the team leader explains the plan for organising a competition. The explanation includes several tasks, deadlines, and reasons for the decisions. You want to make sure you understand the plan correctly and show that you are engaged. Which action would be most effective?', 'Communication', 'Listening', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('fe8b61df-ea82-5452-8c83-ac050ea067dd', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785353', 'You volunteer at a charity. The managers want to make the weekly announcements more interesting so that staff actually listen to them. What is the best way to creatively encourage staff to listen to the announcements?', 'Creative Problem Solving', 'Creativity', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('14a89caf-39e6-5111-a996-4832e2aab736', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785358', 'You organise a birthday surprise for a friend, and several people offer to help. Everyone wants to take the fun jobs like decorating and choosing music, but no one volunteers for the basic admin tasks like organising food delivery and sending reminders. You want to ensure the roles are allocated in a way that gets the surprise organised quickly and effectively. Which approach would be most effective?', 'Collaboration', 'Leadership', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('a04f34de-3275-5be2-819f-a8ca376ce8e3', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785374', 'You and your friends are preparing food for a small neighbourhood event. Two friends start disagreeing about how the food should be arranged on the table. The argument is slowing everyone down. What is the best way to deal with the conflict?', 'Collaboration', 'Teamwork', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('8e8da4f5-dcf2-5c19-af58-fd994509b25e', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785383', 'You and some classmates are practicing for a class presentation. To pass with a good grade, every member of the group needs to present. One member of your team struggles to speak confidently and apologises for “messing everything up.” He looks embarrassed and suggests skipping his part completely. The group still has time to improve, and you want them to succeed. What is the most effective thing to say to support your teammate?', 'Self-management', 'Adapting', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('3453d72f-abea-547d-a3be-7b3483747daa', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785385', 'You have just started an internship. Your supervisor gives you some tasks on a piece of paper: Task Ideal timeline Notes Prepare a report End of day Needs to be perfect Respond to emails Within 20 minutes No mistakes allowed Consider new ideas Anytime this week Chat to the team about this You do not have time to complete all of the tasks perfectly. What is the best approach to completing these tasks?', 'Self-management', 'Planning', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('6e89f81e-b1d5-529a-a051-29409fc21b16', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785415', 'A junior team member frequently asks you how to complete simple tasks. You want to support her without giving all the answers, so you decide to guide her using questions that help her think independently. What should you do?', 'Collaboration', 'Leadership', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('30362f4c-c549-550b-a43f-b1095de48c93', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785417', 'You are helping a younger relative plan a walking route to his new school. He looks confused when you explain it. You want to explain it visually to make it easier for him to understand. What should you do?', 'Communication', 'Speaking', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('a7293a15-3b48-51fc-84ff-65a5010c612b', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785422', 'You were away from work last week and your boss was covering for you. You have been back for a few days and receive a WhatsApp voice message from the boss that says, “I guess I’ll just keep responding to your customer emails….” The boss’s tone sounds serious. What should you understand from the way she spoke in her voice message?', 'Communication', 'Listening', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('efe24de3-4a66-5444-b25f-13fe751c5aea', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785435', 'You practice for an English language test by completing several practice tests in a row. When you review your results, you notice you do well on questions that ask for a single detail from the text, even when the text is complex. You do not do well on questions that ask you to explain how two ideas in the text relate to each other. What does this pattern show you?', 'Creative Problem Solving', 'Problem Solving', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('11c06a9f-c55d-5be8-ac8a-af1ecdc87c30', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785449', 'Your department at work wants to introduce a new weekly lunch time activity to improve team engagement. Before your department decides on whether to do this permanently, you want to prototype it to test how it works. What should you do?', 'Creative Problem Solving', 'Creativity', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('ec9d7335-a272-5b30-827e-bad2de9d81f1', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785456', 'You have started to lose motivation in a subject you find difficult, and your grades are getting worse. To improve, you want to involve others so you can make a realistic plan to get back on track. What should you do?', 'Self-management', 'Planning', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('a9b8d4b2-1e55-56c2-809f-8c2ffd5bf705', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785461', 'Your team at work is reviewing a process that has been used for along time. Everyone follows the same steps in the process, but it is complicated and no one really knows why it was designed this way. Your manager asks you to improve the process. What should you do?', 'Creative Problem Solving', 'Creativity', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('332d6ab2-fd1f-5395-8a36-3f7721cbadfb', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785468', 'You have school during the day, a part-time job after school, and you help look after your younger siblings in the evenings. You also want to make sure you see your friends at least once or twice a week, as this helps you to relax. Recently you have been feeling overwhelmed, and you are not sure how to manage all your responsibilities. You think it is because you aren’t structuring your time properly. What should you do to manage your workload effectively?', 'Self-management', 'Planning', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('c3458a04-05cf-5206-ad8a-6d77db168747', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785479', 'You have started earning money from a part-time job, but after a few months, you realise you keep losing track of how much you have spent. You want to feel more in control of your spending. What is the most effective way to track your money?', 'Self-management', 'Adapting', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('571f868e-7817-5a99-a17a-cfe4b6cc47c6', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785484', 'You are leading a team preparing a presentation for your class, due next Monday. This week, several teammates have been overwhelmed with other work. Two members have submitted their presentations late, and another says they are too stressed to rehearse. You want to motivate the group so that everyone feels more positive and committed, and the team can present on time. What is the best way to help the group succeed?', 'Collaboration', 'Leadership', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('73272dd7-0710-5964-a409-3fd08debaad4', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785485', 'You are reviewing sources for a group assignment. A classmate recommends an article that strongly supports one side of a debate. When you read it, you notice the writer only includes examples that support one viewpoint. No other views are considered. You want to show the group that the article may contain bias. Which action would best achieve this?', 'Communication', 'Listening', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('98e4e618-e9d2-531a-9951-a5ac65a67932', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785487', 'You are leading a short meeting about a work presentation due tomorrow. Two colleagues start blaming each other for missing information, and the discussion becomes tense. You want to keep communication constructive so the team can resolve the issue. What should you do?', 'Communication', 'Speaking', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('de4342f2-256e-53a7-9bd2-066be2001721', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785488', 'Your phone has started losing battery very quickly, even when you are not using it much. You suspect that a game on your phone might be causing the battery to drain faster than normal. You want to test this idea in a structured way to see whether that game is responsible. What should you do to test this idea in a structured way?', 'Creative Problem Solving', 'Problem Solving', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('4c7a10e6-b2b6-5772-951a-912e7eeb3d21', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'c853cbf2-3ad0-5025-b0ca-cdc0f902db5e', '100002785490', 'You are working in a small team in a shop. Tomorrow is expected to be very busy. Two team members have said they might be late. There is also a new staff member joining the team, Ayah. You want to work out the potential problems and prepare to address them. What should you do?', 'Self-management', 'Adapting', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('d54fdcf3-1bfb-5600-aad8-d2958502c7ce', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785095', 'Investigating fish population size The following stimulus has 2 questions. This is the 1 st . You work in a pet shop. You notice some new tropical fish are dying in their water tank. Your boss suggests that it might be because of changes in the water''s concentration of dissolved oxygen (mg/L). She asks you to check. You do some research and find a graph showing the relationship between dissolved oxygen concentration in different fish tanks, and the number of live tropical fish surviving in each tank. The food supply and temperature of each tank is kept the same. <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;3', 'Interpret evidence and data scientifically', 'Using graphs and models to interpret the world', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('4b24b833-bdd4-5fec-9858-007078260547', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785099', 'Testing how sugars can help make extra fluffy bread The following stimulus has 3 questions. This is the 1 st . You work in a bakery and want to make extra fluffy bread for your favourite customer. You know yeast makes dough rise by producing carbon dioxide (CO 2 ) when mixed with sugar. You have 3 types of sugar on the shelf: glucose sucrose (regular sugar) starch (from flour) <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;3355596', 'Interpret evidence and data scientifically', 'Using graphs and models to interpret the world', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('52af78c1-5dc8-582b-93e5-31e624375f58', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '12b7a968-98eb-5a3f-8f6f-421fbaf0414e', '100002785483', 'مقتطف من مقالة بحثيّة – تأثير التّعليم ثنائيّ اللّغة في التّطور المعرفي للأطفال الفقرة تقول الدكتورة ليلى منصور، باحثةٌ في علم النفس التربوي وعضوٌ في فريق دراسةٍ بجامعة هارفارد حول أثر ثنائية اللغة على القدرات المعرفية: "أجدُ أنّ التعلّم بلغتين لا يزيدُ اللسانَ فصاحةً فحسب، بل يوسّعُ للطّالب أبوابَ التواصل، ويُمهّد له مسالكَ أرحب في التعليم الجامعي والفرص المهنية، ولا سيّما في البيئات المتعدّدة الثقافات". ١ وعلى صعيدٍ موازٍ، تكشف بياناتٌ وإحصاءاتٌ من سوق العمل الأوروبي عن طلبٍ بيّن على الكفايات اللغوية؛ إذ كانت الإنجليزية مطلوبةً في ٢٢% من إعلانات الوظائف سنة ٢٠٢١. كما تُظهر تقاريرُ المفوضية الأوروبية ضمن رصدها لمؤشرات سوق العمل أنّ الموظفين متعددي اللغات يتقاضون أجورًا أعلى بنسبةٍ تتراوح بين ٥% و١٥% مقارنةً بغيرهم. ٢ ويذهبُ الباحثون في الأدبيات التّربوية إلى أنّ التّعليمَ ثنائيَّ اللغة لا يقتصر أثرُه على صقل المهارات اللغوية، بل يمتدّ إلى بنًى معرفيةٍ أشمل؛ مثل الذّاكرة العاملة والمرونة المعرفيّة والانتباه الانتقائي. ويُفسِّر أصحابُ هذا الاتّجاه تلك الفروق بمفهوم “التّحكّم المعرفيّ”؛ أي قدرة الدّماغ على تنظيم الانتباه وتبديل المهام بكفاءة. فالتّدرّب المتواصل على الانتقال بين لغتين يُنشِّط الجهاز التّنفيذي في الدّماغ ويُقوّيه، بما يعضدّ حلّ المشكلات ويُنمّي التّفكير النّقدي، ويجعل المتعلّم أقدر على انتقاء المعلومة وصدِّ المُشتّتات. ٣ يُقصدُ بالتّعليم “ثنائيِّ اللغة” أن يتلقّى المتعلّمُ تعلّمه بلغتين بدلًا من لغةٍ واحدة، بحيث يكتسب القراءة والكتابة، ويتعامل مع المحتوى المعرفيّ والأكاديميّ بكلتا اللّغتين على نحوٍ متوازن. وقد قامت الدراسةُ المشارُ إليها بمقارنة مجموعةٍ تلقّت تعليمًا ثنائيَّ اللغة بأخرى أحاديّةِ اللّغة، مع توظيف اختباراتٍ متعدّدة لقياس الذّاكرة العاملة والمرونة المعرفيّة والانتباه الانتقائيّ، في محاولةٍ لضبط الفروق وإرجاعها إلى طبيعة البرنامج التّعليميّ لا إلى المصادفة. ٤ وتتبدّى نتائجُ ذلك في صورٍ قريبةٍ من الخبرة الصفّية اليوميّة: إذ سَجّل الأطفالُ في البرامج ثنائيّة اللّغة درجاتٍ أعلى في اختبارات الذّاكرة والمرونة المعرفيّة، وأظهروا قدرةً أجود على التّركيز وتجاهل المُشتّتات. ولتقريب المعنى، فإنّ الطفل الذي اعتاد التحوّل بين نظامين لغويين يصبح في مواقف التعلّم أكثر تمرّسًا في حجب المثيرات الجانبية حين تتزاحم الأصوات أو تتكاثر الإشارات، وأسرع في تبديل “قاعدة العمل” عند الانتقال بين مهمتين متتاليتين، وهو ما ينسجم مع فكرة تقوية التنظيم التنفيذي للانتباه. وهذه المظاهر، وإن قُدّمت في قالبٍ تجريبيّ، تنعكس على مهاراتٍ عمليةٍ يمارسها الطفلُ في التّعلم، من تثبيت المعلومات، إلى الانتقال بين المهمّات، إلى الانتباه الانتقائيّ حين تتزاحمُ المؤثرات. ٥ غير أنّ النّظرَ في هذا الملفّ لا يكتمل بذكر المنافع وحدها؛ فثمّة كلفةٌ تنظيميّةٌ وتحدّياتٌ واقعيّةٌ تفرضُ على صانعي السّياسات التّربويّة حساباتٍ دقيقة. فمن أبرز ما يواجه برامج التّعليم ثنائيّ اللغة: نقصُ المعلّمين المتخصّصين، وصعوبةُ بناء مناهج متوازنة بين اللّغتين، وضرورةُ مراعاة تباين الخلفيات اللّغوية والمعرفيّة للطّلاب. وتُظهر بعض التجارب في أنظمةٍ تعليميةٍ متعدّدة اللغات أنّ نجاح هذا المسار يرتبط بوضوح “خارطة التنفيذ” (متى تُستعمل لغةُ الأم، ومتى تتدرّج اللغةُ الثانية، وكيف تُضبط جودة المواد والتقويم). وفي المقابل، يُشير بعض الباحثين إلى احتمال ظهور تأخّرٍ لغويٍّ مبكّر لدى بعض الأطفال عند التعرض للغتين قبل رسوخ الأولى؛ غير أنّ المتابعات طويلة الأمد في كثيرٍ من الأدبي', 'Reading comprehension', 'Understanding Meaning', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('d956a572-cb1b-51c0-bb74-b8adc7e206b2', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785234', 'Welcome to the G12++ Scientific Thinking section Here, you can show how confident you are in applying critical thinking to solve scientific problems. You have 90 minutes to answer exam questions. All questions are multiple-choice questions. At the end, there will be a 5-minute survey. How can you do your best? Manage your time: <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&q', NULL, NULL, 'D1', 0, 'active'),
  ('38ff905e-261e-5023-ba95-5bf5e98fe9bf', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785003', 'You notice that your leftover rice spoils faster when it is left on the table after dinner, even when the nights are cool. When the rice is placed in a sealed container and kept in the fridge, it lasts longer and does not develop a sour smell as quickly. Which hypothesis best explains why the rice spoils more slowly in the fridge?', 'Explain phenomena scientifically', 'Formulating or Selecting the best hypothesis', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('bb36cb3c-01e1-527f-bb8d-91216d5295f0', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785005', 'A nurse in a small town suggested that people who washed their hands more often had fewer stomach illnesses. To test this, she gave soap and hygiene lessons to half the families in the town. The other families in the town were not given soap or hygiene lessons. After 1 month, she recorded the number of stomach illness cases in both groups. What is being tested in this investigation?', 'Explain phenomena scientifically', 'Formulating or Selecting the best hypothesis', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('dfe83f4f-79ab-5fca-84da-9dc9513c5433', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785007', 'You have just moved to a new town. You are curious about which buildings would be quieter. You decide to compare noise levels inside 2 buildings. Building A Building B . You observe that building B (surrounded by buildings) has higher average noise levels indoors than building A (surrounded by open space). What is the most reasonable explanation?', 'Explain phenomena scientifically', 'Formulating or Selecting the best hypothesis', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('40b0acd8-e372-5ba2-b57c-66a59cf6dedf', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785008', 'You volunteer with the local city government. They ask you to find out whether using solar-powered streetlights reduces the number of night-time car accidents on a busy road. Which of the following tests would be best for exploring the effect of the new solar streetlights? Count the number of night-time accidents on the road...', 'Evaluate and design scientific inquiry', 'Understanding variables and validity', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('786b8931-63fd-555d-b10a-78866807093a', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785010', 'You are painting a special gift for a friend. You want to find out which paintbrush gives you the smoothest lines. You use the same paint and paper for painting: 10 lines with a thin brush 10 with a medium brush 10 with a thick brush You count how many lines in each group look smooth (rather than wobbly). <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559731&quot;:0,&quot;335559737&quot;:0,&quot;335562764&quot;:2,&quot;335562765&quot;:1,&quot;335562766&quot;:4', 'Evaluate and design scientific inquiry', 'Understanding variables and validity', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('621479f8-1b9f-5baf-87a4-d3c8712a1a88', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785015', 'You grow 2 small plants in your room. You want to test how different conditions affect their growth. The plants get the same amount of water and sunlight. You place a clear plastic bag over 1 plant, and leave the other plant uncovered. The results after 1 week are shown in the diagram. You get the same results when you repeat the test. &nbs', 'Explain phenomena scientifically', 'Formulating or Selecting the best hypothesis', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('83dd313b-83c8-5356-a1da-2421abba3588', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785016', 'You notice that cars roll down a hill faster when the tyres are fully inflated. What is the most likely reason for this?', 'Explain phenomena scientifically', 'Using everyday application of scientific thinking', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('c4c099b6-a29f-513d-9db4-7d25267fab1a', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785017', 'A child with 2 healthy parents is diagnosed with cystic fibrosis, an inherited recessive condition. Neither parent shows symptoms of cystic fibrosis. Glossary: Inheritance is the passing of traits from parent to child. Traits pass through genes. Genes come in pairs. Each gene in the pair is called an allele. Al', 'Explain phenomena scientifically', 'Using everyday application of scientific thinking', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('00f15224-b391-5b85-a179-0f5411ccd323', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785020', 'You help your cousin build a ramp for toy cars at home. You want to understand how a car''s weight affects the distance it travels across the carpet after it goes down the ramp. You decide to do a test: Attempt Distance (cm) 1st time 20.1 2nd time 22.3 3rd time 18.2 You measure the distance that a blue car travels across the carpet after it goes down the ramp. You repeat the test twice with that car. You write down the results: Car Weight (N) </p', 'Interpret evidence and data scientifically', 'Interpreting and inferring scientific data', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('b3704ac6-9ad5-5b4b-940b-f0e9358e0bbe', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785022', 'Your geography class studies air pollution in your city. The city has: 5 residential areas (less pollution) 1 major highway (high pollution) 2 industrial zones (very high pollution) You and your classmates place sensors at 12 schools in residential areas, all evenly spread across the city. You set the sensors to measure air pollution every hour for 1 month. Which option best explains how the study could be improved to obtain results which represent air quality across your city?', 'Evaluate and design scientific inquiry', 'Evaluating scientific methods', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('28a91339-c863-5a08-ba8c-5ea8eb31f024', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785025', 'A tropical forest lost 40% of its tree cover in 10 years. Researchers found a harmful cycle caused by deforestation (cutting down trees): The loss of trees meant soil temperature increased and moisture decreased. This slowed down decomposers and reduced nutrients in the soil, so plants grew more slowly. Fewer new plants meant even less tree cover, which lead to more local flooding as the ground absorbed less rain. They also found some populations of seed-spreading animals decreased because they rely on f', 'Evaluate and design scientific inquiry', 'Comprehending and analyzing scientific texts', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('0b0df454-e319-5f1c-bb72-bd1d85bcaef0', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785032', 'In a science project, you learn that greenhouse gases trap heat in the Earth''s atmosphere, causing global warming. The table shows some data on 3 greenhouse gases which are the main contributors to global warming. Gas Carbon dioxide CO 2 Methane CH 4 Nitrous oxide N 2 O Amount (by weight, %) 99 0.7 0.02 Contribution to warming (%) 74.8 19.5 5.6 Average lifetime in the atmosphere (years) 500+ 12 121 Main source Burning of fossil fuels Agriculture Fertilisers Based on the table, why would reducing methane emissions be a quick, temporary way to slow global warming?', 'Explain phenomena scientifically', 'Using everyday application of scientific thinking', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('22b16ee7-9c81-5bc0-bb2f-d706c5249b70', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785046', 'In response to global warming, the world is moving towards sustainable solutions, such as solar energy. Solar energy can be unreliable – sometimes it makes too much energy, and other times it makes none. Scientists are trying to store extra solar energy as liquid air. It can then be released as a gas to regenerate energy when needed (e.g. at night). From the graph, why is storing energy as liquid air better than storing it as gas?', 'Explain phenomena scientifically', 'Using everyday application of scientific thinking', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('523c553f-8169-5ecb-957c-87da8bf0ab31', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785051', 'One effect of global warming is that ice in the polar regions is melting. Your science teacher wants to show the class how temperature affects the rate of ice melting. She measures the time taken for ice blocks to melt at a fixed temperature. The ice blocks are all the same size. Trial Time to melt (minutes) 1 42 2 45 3 44 4 91 5 43 Which action would best improve the reliability and validity of this experiment?', 'Evaluate and design scientific inquiry', 'Repeating experiments and outliers', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('fa8a4887-84c7-5216-88de-536bc5f12098', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785072', 'Your science teacher shows you a video about how air temperature affects the speed of sound. The video shows an experiment using a speaker and a microphone. The speaker makes a sound that echoes against a wall that is 10 metres away. The microphone detects the echo. The researchers record the following data: Trial Air Temperature ( o C) Time for echo (s) 1 0 0.058 2 10 0.057 3 20 0.056 4 30 0.055 <', 'Evaluate and design scientific inquiry', 'Evaluating scientific methods', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('6608d51a-b4de-5d64-9a41-5d2b96049383', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785073', 'While hiking with your class, you lean forward as you walk uphill. Leaning forward maintains the centre of gravity between your feet, offering more stability. In which of the following scenarios is the same principle of stability applied?', 'Explain phenomena scientifically', 'Using everyday application of scientific thinking', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('3c265109-156f-56f3-9307-3531550548a5', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785075', 'Cricket is a bat and ball game that involves hitting the ball as far as possible. You are a cricket coach testing different materials for cricket balls to find out how far each ball will travel when hit with different batting forces. The graph below shows the distance travelled by balls made of 3 different materials (A, B, C). You want a ball that maximises distance for beginner players (low batting force, around 350 N) and professional players (high batting force, around 600 N). Based on the graph, which ball material should you choose?', 'Interpret evidence and data scientifically', 'Using graphs and models to interpret the world', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('60c7c2b1-e5c1-5521-a7f8-f3b42e016a21', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785079', 'You hear that a big storm is coming to your town. The graph shows how long the storm cloud will take to reach your town from various distances, if wind speed is constant at 20 km/hr. Your weather app says the storm cloud is 50 km away. For the first part of its journey, the wind speed will be 20 km/hr When the cloud is 20 km away, the wind speed will increase to 40 km/hr for the rest of the journey. Based on this information, what is the most likely estimate for the total time it will take the storm cloud to reach your town?', 'Interpret evidence and data scientifically', 'Using graphs and models to interpret the world', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('1aeb2b36-5e09-5b6c-95f1-52f5c958ea6f', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785080', 'After a storm, your local city government replaces part of a damaged concrete bridge with a metal walkway that is the same shape and thickness as the old concrete bridge. During winter, people say the metal feels much colder to touch than the concrete, even though both have been exposed to the same cold weather overnight. You are asked to explain this observation using physics. Which hypothesis best explains why the metal walkway feels colder than the concrete bridge?', 'Explain phenomena scientifically', 'Formulating or Selecting the best hypothesis', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('54f0debf-dac5-5c4c-8e93-e89bf7eb8530', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785083', 'A vaccination programme was launched in 2020 to reduce a contagious illness in a small town. A public health team is evaluating it. The graph below shows their findings: Based on the graph, which statement is best supported by the data?', 'Interpret evidence and data scientifically', 'Using graphs and models to interpret the world', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('1fc0940e-cd6f-548e-b180-873c7b309872', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785085', 'You read online that, in many parts of the world, adults cannot digest milk because their bodies stop making an enzyme called lactase after childhood. People who can digest milk as adults have a gene variant that allows them to keep making lactase. You find this table of data, collected from 4 different regions: Region Percentage of adults who can digest milk (%) Diet Main type of agriculture in the region Northern Europe 90 Milk and dairy products Animal farming East Asia 10 Rice and vegetables Crop farming East Africa 65 Milk and meat Animal farming South America 25 Corn and beans Mixed farming Which hypothe', 'Evaluate and design scientific inquiry', 'Testing hypothesis using evidence-based reasoning', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('9b3c93c1-3220-5479-a0db-6e7c8b4a3d8a', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785088', 'You are a journalist reporting on climate change. You read that some halogen gases can damage the ozone layer that protects the Earth''s surface from harmful UV (light) rays. Scientists measured damage to the ozone layer (graph 1) and worked out which man-made chemicals and naturally occurring processes(e.g. volcanic eruptions) contributed to ozone damage. They then banned the man-made chemicals through a gradual phaseout from 1987 (graph 2). Graph 1: <IMG src="%SERVER.GRAPHICS%topicresources/289292/halogen_ozone_graph_1.png" class="" style="display: inline; height: 280px; width: 450px" alt="Halogen ozone graph 1.png', 'Explain phenomena scientifically', 'Using everyday application of scientific thinking', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('7ea4a6e0-6a3a-52e7-85e4-83f64a62c619', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785091', 'Your school headteacher asks you to find out if speed bumps near the school would reduce the kinetic energy of cars as they pass. You stand at the school entrance and use an instant measuring device to measure the speeds of 30 cars. You collect these data 1 week before and 1 month after the speed bumps are added. You assume each car''s mass is 1,200 kg. You calculate the average kinetic energy of the cars. You conclude that “speed bumps significantly reduce the kinetic energy of cars passing the school.” <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559', 'Evaluate and design scientific inquiry', 'Evaluating scientific methods', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('21fe84ea-c196-560f-99ea-2b868424ba0d', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785101', 'Testing how sugars can help make extra fluffy bread The following stimulus has 3 questions. This is the 2 nd . You work in a bakery and want to make extra fluffy bread for your favourite customer. You know yeast makes dough rise by producing carbon dioxide (CO 2 ) when mixed with sugar. You have 3 types of sugar on the shelf: glucose sucrose (regular sugar) starch (from flour) <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;3355596', 'Interpret evidence and data scientifically', 'Using graphs and models to interpret the world', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('b78a7eb7-8ad4-5de8-9e91-e7d2e995d44f', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785103', 'Testing how sugars can help make extra fluffy bread The following stimulus has 3 questions. This is the 3 rd . You work in a bakery and want to make extra fluffy bread for your favourite customer. You know yeast makes dough rise by producing carbon dioxide (CO 2 ) when mixed with sugar. You have 3 types of sugar on the shelf: glucose sucrose (regular sugar) starch (from flour) <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;3355596', 'Interpret evidence and data scientifically', 'Using graphs and models to interpret the world', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('5a145a3f-841e-5e77-a779-8d6fe210ff41', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785104', 'Testing tablet dissolving times under different conditions The following stimulus has 2 questions. This is the 1 st . In a chemistry class, you test how quickly a vitamin tablet dissolves in water at different temperatures. You record the time it takes (in seconds) for the tablet to fully dissolve in 100 mL of water. The results are shown below: Which interpretation is most correct about the effect of increasing temperature on dissolving time, based on the trend of the graph?', 'Interpret evidence and data scientifically', 'Using graphs and models to interpret the world', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('479a1fc8-b3b4-5661-bb71-2fcd34f15142', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785106', 'Testing tablet dissolving times under different conditions The following stimulus has 2 questions. This is the 2 nd . In a chemistry class, you test how quickly a vitamin tablet dissolves in water at different temperatures. You record the time it takes (in seconds) for the tablet to fully dissolve in 100 mL of water. The results are shown below: To improve reliability, you decide to repeat the experiment another 2 times, exactly as before. You get nearly the same results, but find that on the final repeat, the tablet took 200 seconds to dissolve at 30 o C. How should you treat this 30 o C value?', 'Evaluate and design scientific inquiry', 'Repeating experiments and outliers', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('7f9fa652-51dd-5c57-80e3-54975c518863', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785107', 'Understanding pH indicators to help tomato plants thrive The following stimulus has 3 questions. This is the 1 st . You want to know if the soil in your pot is good for planting tomatoes. You buy 4 indicators and add them to cups containing soil and water mixed together. Indicators are liquids that change colour. Depending on the colour change, they tell you how acidic (low pH, like lemon juice) or alkaline (high pH, like soap) the soil is. Details of your indicators are shown below: Indicator &', 'Interpret evidence and data scientifically', 'Interpreting and inferring scientific data', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('8e7e5ca7-ed8d-5917-a04b-ae4d243b9a38', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785108', 'Understanding pH indicators to help tomato plants thrive The following stimulus has 3 questions. This is the 2 nd . You want to know if the soil in your pot is good for planting tomatoes. You buy 4 indicators and add them to cups containing soil and water mixed together. Indicators are liquids that change colour. Depending on the colour change, they tell you how acidic (low pH, like lemon juice) or alkaline (high pH, like soap) the soil is. Details of your indicators are shown below: Indicator &nbs', 'Interpret evidence and data scientifically', 'Interpreting and inferring scientific data', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('9bd2123d-4c28-5e2e-a7c8-e8b65a92c3e6', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', 'd9eb8503-a733-5a58-a8c0-7aceedcbe97e', '100002785111', 'Investigating water bottle smells The following stimulus has 2 questions. This is the 2 nd . Your classmate wants to test whether reusable plastic water bottles develop smells faster than disposable plastic bottles. She fills 1 reusable bottle and 1 disposable bottle with tap water She leaves the bottles in her backpack for 2 weeks Every 2 days, she smells each bottle and rates the smell from 0 (none) to 5 (strong). <p data-ccp-props="{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559731&quot;:0,&quot;335559737&quot;:0,&quot;335562764&quot;:2,&quot;335562765&quot;:1,&quot;335562766&quot;:4,&quot;335562767&quot;:0,&quot;335562768&quot;:4,&quot;335562769&quot;:0', 'Evaluate and design scientific inquiry', 'Using scientific processes and investigation', 'D3', 1, 'active'),
  ('3cf31ddf-70c4-5838-b3f6-88f293153ffc', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '12b7a968-98eb-5a3f-8f6f-421fbaf0414e', '100002785209', 'يومٌ من المستقبل الفقرة استيقظتُ على نبرةٍ مألوفةٍ طال اغترابُها عن سمعي… نداءُ الباعة في أزقّةِ دمشقَ القديمة. فتحتُ النافذةَ، فإذا بالمدينةِ تتجلّى لي كما لو أنّها تُستعاد من الرّماد: نظيفةٌ، مضيئةٌ، تنبضُ بالحياة. لا حواجزَ ولا خيام؛ بل أشجارٌ على الأرصفة كأنّها حُرّاسُ ظلٍّ، وأطفالٌ يمضون إلى مدارسَ جديدةٍ تحمل أسماءَ الشعراءِ والعلماءِ. خُيّل إليّ أنّني أحلم، فبدأ عقلي يفتّش عن دليلٍ يردّ الحلمَ إلى الواقع؛ غير أنّ الهواءَ كان حقيقيًّا، ورائحةَ الخبزِ الساخن كانت تُغري باليقظة، وتتركُ في صدري دهشةً ممزوجةً بالفرحِ والحنين. ١ خرجتُ إلى الشارعِ بخطواتٍ متردّدة، كأنّ الطريقَ يختبرُ صدقي، فشعرتُ أنّ كلَّ حجرٍ يعرفني ويحفظُ اسمي. ومع كلِّ مشهدٍ كنتُ أوازن بين ما أراه الآن وما خزّنته ذاكرتي من شقوقٍ وغبار: هل تغيّر الشّكلُ وحده، أم تبدّل المعنى؟ وعلى الجدران لافتاتٌ لا تُعلن شيئًا بقدر ما تُخاطبُ الداخل، مكتوبةٌ بعبارةٍ واحدة: “مرحَبًا بالعائدين… الوطن ينتظركم.” ٢ دخلتُ مدرستي الجديدة، فاستقبلتني معلّمةٌ بابتسامةٍ دافئة. على الجدران لوحاتٌ رسمها طلابٌ من مختلفِ المناطق: البحرُ، الجبالُ، الحقولُ، والمنازلُ التي بُنيت من جديد. في الصفّ جلستْ بجانبي فتاةٌ من حلب، وصبيٌّ من حمص، وضحكنا معًا ونحن نحكي عن أحلامِنا القادمة. لم يعد أحدٌ يسأل "من أين أنت؟"، بل "ماذا ستفعل لتجعل وطنك أجمل؟"؛ سؤالٌ يُبدّل زاوية النظر: من تعريف الذات بالأصل إلى تعريفها بالأثر. ٣ في نهايةِ اليوم، اجتمعنا في السّاحة نرفعُ علمَ الوطن، وأصواتُنا تمتزجُ بالأمل. عندها أدركتُ أن الحلمَ الذي عاش فينا كلَّ تلك السنوات لم يكن مستحيلًا، وأنّ الاجتماع لا يكتمل برمزٍ وحده، بل بفكرةٍ مشتركةٍ تُترجم عملًا: أن ننتمي معًا كي نبني مستقبلًا موحّدًا. فهمتُ أيضًا أنّ الأمل ليس عاطفةً عابرة؛ إنه موقفٌ يحتاج إلى مسؤوليّةٍ كي لا يعود مجرّد صورة. ٤ وقبل أن تغيبَ الشّمس، نظرتُ إلى السّماءِ، فشعرتُ بشيءٍ من الطّمأنينة. قلتُ في نفسي: "هذا اليوم سيأتي، إن لم يكن غدًا فبعد غدٍ، لكنّه سيأتي… لأنّنا لم نتوقف عن الحلم." فتحتُ عينيّ لأكتشف أنّني كنتُ أكتب مشهدًا من الخيال… مشهدًا اخترتُه ليكون نافذةً نطلّ منها على غدٍ أجمل، ثم نعود لنصنعه بالأمل والعمل. ٥ استنادًا إلى الفقرة الأولى، في اللّحظة التي ينكشف فيها مشهدُ المدينة للرّاوي، ما الحالة الشّعوريّة الأبرز التي تهيمن عليه؟', 'Reading comprehension', 'Understanding Meaning', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('ee3a96c6-0b52-56a1-9556-15e2a5308dba', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '12b7a968-98eb-5a3f-8f6f-421fbaf0414e', '100002785223', 'يومٌ من المستقبل الفقرة استيقظتُ على نبرةٍ مألوفةٍ طال اغترابُها عن سمعي… نداءُ الباعة في أزقّةِ دمشقَ القديمة. فتحتُ النافذةَ، فإذا بالمدينةِ تتجلّى لي كما لو أنّها تُستعاد من الرّماد: نظيفةٌ، مضيئةٌ، تنبضُ بالحياة. لا حواجزَ ولا خيام؛ بل أشجارٌ على الأرصفة كأنّها حُرّاسُ ظلٍّ، وأطفالٌ يمضون إلى مدارسَ جديدةٍ تحمل أسماءَ الشعراءِ والعلماءِ. خُيّل إليّ أنّني أحلم، فبدأ عقلي يفتّش عن دليلٍ يردّ الحلمَ إلى الواقع؛ غير أنّ الهواءَ كان حقيقيًّا، ورائحةَ الخبزِ الساخن كانت تُغري باليقظة، وتتركُ في صدري دهشةً ممزوجةً بالفرحِ والحنين. ١ خرجتُ إلى الشارعِ بخطواتٍ متردّدة، كأنّ الطريقَ يختبرُ صدقي، فشعرتُ أنّ كلَّ حجرٍ يعرفني ويحفظُ اسمي. ومع كلِّ مشهدٍ كنتُ أوازن بين ما أراه الآن وما خزّنته ذاكرتي من شقوقٍ وغبار: هل تغيّر الشّكلُ وحده، أم تبدّل المعنى؟ وعلى الجدران لافتاتٌ لا تُعلن شيئًا بقدر ما تُخاطبُ الداخل، مكتوبةٌ بعبارةٍ واحدة: “مرحَبًا بالعائدين… الوطن ينتظركم.” ٢ دخلتُ مدرستي الجديدة، فاستقبلتني معلّمةٌ بابتسامةٍ دافئة. على الجدران لوحاتٌ رسمها طلابٌ من مختلفِ المناطق: البحرُ، الجبالُ، الحقولُ، والمنازلُ التي بُنيت من جديد. في الصفّ جلستْ بجانبي فتاةٌ من حلب، وصبيٌّ من حمص، وضحكنا معًا ونحن نحكي عن أحلامِنا القادمة. لم يعد أحدٌ يسأل "من أين أنت؟"، بل "ماذا ستفعل لتجعل وطنك أجمل؟"؛ سؤالٌ يُبدّل زاوية النظر: من تعريف الذات بالأصل إلى تعريفها بالأثر. ٣ في نهايةِ اليوم، اجتمعنا في السّاحة نرفعُ علمَ الوطن، وأصواتُنا تمتزجُ بالأمل. عندها أدركتُ أن الحلمَ الذي عاش فينا كلَّ تلك السنوات لم يكن مستحيلًا، وأنّ الاجتماع لا يكتمل برمزٍ وحده، بل بفكرةٍ مشتركةٍ تُترجم عملًا: أن ننتمي معًا كي نبني مستقبلًا موحّدًا. فهمتُ أيضًا أنّ الأمل ليس عاطفةً عابرة؛ إنه موقفٌ يحتاج إلى مسؤوليّةٍ كي لا يعود مجرّد صورة. ٤ وقبل أن تغيبَ الشّمس، نظرتُ إلى السّماءِ، فشعرتُ بشيءٍ من الطّمأنينة. قلتُ في نفسي: "هذا اليوم سيأتي، إن لم يكن غدًا فبعد غدٍ، لكنّه سيأتي… لأنّنا لم نتوقف عن الحلم." فتحتُ عينيّ لأكتشف أنّني كنتُ أكتب مشهدًا من الخيال… مشهدًا اخترتُه ليكون نافذةً نطلّ منها على غدٍ أجمل، ثم نعود لنصنعه بالأمل والعمل. ٥ أيُّ فكرةٍ محوريّةٍ يُعزّزها النّصّ حول الأمل وصناعة المستقبل؟', 'Reading comprehension', 'Understanding Meaning', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
  ('a44ce5b1-afb3-58a1-be29-e3330f0afee5', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '12b7a968-98eb-5a3f-8f6f-421fbaf0414e', '100002785227', 'يومٌ من المستقبل الفقرة استيقظتُ على نبرةٍ مألوفةٍ طال اغترابُها عن سمعي… نداءُ الباعة في أزقّةِ دمشقَ القديمة. فتحتُ النافذةَ، فإذا بالمدينةِ تتجلّى لي كما لو أنّها تُستعاد من الرّماد: نظيفةٌ، مضيئةٌ، تنبضُ بالحياة. لا حواجزَ ولا خيام؛ بل أشجارٌ على الأرصفة كأنّها حُرّاسُ ظلٍّ، وأطفالٌ يمضون إلى مدارسَ جديدةٍ تحمل أسماءَ الشعراءِ والعلماءِ. خُيّل إليّ أنّني أحلم، فبدأ عقلي يفتّش عن دليلٍ يردّ الحلمَ إلى الواقع؛ غير أنّ الهواءَ كان حقيقيًّا، ورائحةَ الخبزِ الساخن كانت تُغري باليقظة، وتتركُ في صدري دهشةً ممزوجةً بالفرحِ والحنين. ١ خرجتُ إلى الشارعِ بخطواتٍ متردّدة، كأنّ الطريقَ يختبرُ صدقي، فشعرتُ أنّ كلَّ حجرٍ يعرفني ويحفظُ اسمي. ومع كلِّ مشهدٍ كنتُ أوازن بين ما أراه الآن وما خزّنته ذاكرتي من شقوقٍ وغبار: هل تغيّر الشّكلُ وحده، أم تبدّل المعنى؟ وعلى الجدران لافتاتٌ لا تُعلن شيئًا بقدر ما تُخاطبُ الداخل، مكتوبةٌ بعبارةٍ واحدة: “مرحَبًا بالعائدين… الوطن ينتظركم.” ٢ دخلتُ مدرستي الجديدة، فاستقبلتني معلّمةٌ بابتسامةٍ دافئة. على الجدران لوحاتٌ رسمها طلابٌ من مختلفِ المناطق: البحرُ، الجبالُ، الحقولُ، والمنازلُ التي بُنيت من جديد. في الصفّ جلستْ بجانبي فتاةٌ من حلب، وصبيٌّ من حمص، وضحكنا معًا ونحن نحكي عن أحلامِنا القادمة. لم يعد أحدٌ يسأل "من أين أنت؟"، بل "ماذا ستفعل لتجعل وطنك أجمل؟"؛ سؤالٌ يُبدّل زاوية النظر: من تعريف الذات بالأصل إلى تعريفها بالأثر. ٣ في نهايةِ اليوم، اجتمعنا في السّاحة نرفعُ علمَ الوطن، وأصواتُنا تمتزجُ بالأمل. عندها أدركتُ أن الحلمَ الذي عاش فينا كلَّ تلك السنوات لم يكن مستحيلًا، وأنّ الاجتماع لا يكتمل برمزٍ وحده، بل بفكرةٍ مشتركةٍ تُترجم عملًا: أن ننتمي معًا كي نبني مستقبلًا موحّدًا. فهمتُ أيضًا أنّ الأمل ليس عاطفةً عابرة؛ إنه موقفٌ يحتاج إلى مسؤوليّةٍ كي لا يعود مجرّد صورة. ٤ وقبل أن تغيبَ الشّمس، نظرتُ إلى السّماءِ، فشعرتُ بشيءٍ من الطّمأنينة. قلتُ في نفسي: "هذا اليوم سيأتي، إن لم يكن غدًا فبعد غدٍ، لكنّه سيأتي… لأنّنا لم نتوقف عن الحلم." فتحتُ عينيّ لأكتشف أنّني كنتُ أكتب مشهدًا من الخيال… مشهدًا اخترتُه ليكون نافذةً نطلّ منها على غدٍ أجمل، ثم نعود لنصنعه بالأمل والعمل. ٥ في سياق النّصّ، ما الدلالة الأبرز لاجتماع طلابٍ من مدنٍ مختلفة ورفعهم العلم معًا؟', 'Reading comprehension', 'Understanding Meaning', 'D2', 1, 'active'),
  ('02d8a19b-9d98-577a-a636-c014a286e530', '3385d4a5-b4c2-5331-a7a9-53a03f3f4869', '12b7a968-98eb-5a3f-8f6f-421fbaf0414e', '100002785314', 'دليلك الذّكيّ لشراء هاتف مستعمل الفقرة في عصرٍ تتسارعُ فيه وتيرة إصدارات الهواتف الذّكيّة بشكلٍ سنويّ، يواجه قطاع عريض من المستهلكين، لا سيّما الشّريحة الطّلابيّة والشّباب، تحدّي المواءمة بين طموحِهم في حيازة أجهزةٍ ذات مواصفات متقدّمة وبين إكراهات الميزانيّة المحدودة. لهذا، أضحى سوق الأجهزة المستعملة خيارًا استراتيجيًّا يزاوج بين توفير المال والحصول على تكنولوجيا مفيدة. فعمليّة اقتناء هاتفٍ مستعملٍ لا تعني حتمًا الإذعان لجهازٍ رديء أو غير موثوق، بل هي خطوة متبصّرة متى ما تمّ التّعامل معها بمنهجيّة وحذر. ١ تشيرُ الدّراسات الاستهلاكيّة إلى أنّ المقتنين يمكنهم استرداد ما يزيد عن ٦٠٪ من الثّمن الأصليّ للهاتف. وهذا المسار لا يقتصر نفعه على التّوفير الماليّ فحسب، بل يساهم أيضًا في تقليص حجم المخلّفات الإلكترونيّة، وهو ما يعكس وعيًا بيئيًّا بات ضرورةً ملحّة. لكنّ الشّراء العشوائيّ دون استقصاء أو تمحيص مسبق قد يُفضي إلى عواقبَ غير مرضية. ٢ لذا، بات من المحتّم على المشتري أن يتّبع خطوات إجرائيّة واضحة. يجب على المشتري أن يحدّد سقفًا لميزانيّته، وأن يستطلع آراء المستخدمين حول النماذج التي أثبتت جدارتها، وعليه أن يتأكّد بدقّة من سلامة البطّارية والشّاشة ووحدة التّصوير. كما ينبغي له أن يستوضح عن سجلّ استخدام الجهاز. ومن التّدابير الاحترازيّة الأخرى، الحرص على أن يتمّ اللّقاء مع البائع في موقع عمومي، ويفضّل طلب نسخة من فاتورة الشّراء الأصليّة أو أي وثيقة تثبت المِلكيّة. ٣ ومن الأهمّية بمكان أن يستوعب المشتري حقوقه. فبعض المحلّات التّجاريّة المتخصّصة تقدّم ضمانًا مؤقتًا قد يصل إلى شهر، ممّا يعطي فرصة لتجربة الجهاز بأمان، وفي ما يخصّ المفاوضات، فمن الأفضل أن تُدار برصانة واحترام متبادل، دون تجاوز للسّقف المالي المحدّد. ٤ في الختام، يتّضح أنّ الشّراء الذّكي لهاتف مستعمل ليس مغامرة غير محسوبة، بل هو فرصة اقتصاديّة حقيقيّة. الأمر لا يتطلّب سوى تخطيط بسيط، والقدرة على طرح الأسئلة الأساسيّة، ومقارنة العروض بشكل نقديّ. فجودة الهاتف لا تقاس دائمًا بسعره، بل بالفائدة التي يقدّمها في حياتك اليومية. ٥ ما الفكرة الأساسيّة الأهم التي يتمحور حولها المقال بأكمله؟', 'Reading comprehension', 'Understanding Meaning', 'D1', 1, 'active'),
